text: Fortin Site is a prehistoric village site located in Oneonta, New York. It was added to the National Register of Historic Places on November 28, 1980.http://www.historicbuildings.us/fortin-site-oneonta-ny/uploadphoto ==References== Category:Archaeological sites in New York (state) Category:National Register of Historic Places in Otsego County, New York Category:Archaeological sites on the National Register of Historic Places in New York (state)
